00:44:10.950 --> 00:44:12.250
Last question.

00:44:12.250 --> 00:44:13.870
&gt;&gt; If I may comment about why
people may not be better at math

00:44:13.870 --> 00:44:16.410
or risk analysis in particular is

00:44:16.410 --> 00:44:18.340
that obviously humans
are risk takers

00:44:18.340 --> 00:44:19.660
and that has obvious advantages.

00:44:19.660 --> 00:44:23.140
If Lindbergh knew the real odds of
his surviving the flight to Paris,

00:44:23.140 --> 00:44:24.440
he wouldn't have done it.

00:44:24.440 --> 00:44:25.740
All right.

00:44:25.740 --> 00:44:27.120
But my real question has to do
with the scratch-off tickets.

00:44:27.120 --> 00:44:33.250
And what is it about the printing
and things that allows you to win?

00:44:33.250 --> 00:44:35.530
OK. You've never told us.

00:44:35.530 --> 00:44:39.510
&gt;&gt; Joseph Mazur: Well, it is a bit
complicated and I really can't.

00:44:39.510 --> 00:44:44.300
[ Laughter ]

00:44:44.300 --> 00:44:45.760
There are schemes.

00:44:45.760 --> 00:44:51.340
All I can say is there are
schemes where you adjust your--

00:44:51.340 --> 00:44:56.460 position:56%
the timing of your buying the ticket
to the place of buying the ticket

00:44:56.460 --> 00:45:00.530
because you would know how many of
those tickets were already bought

00:45:00.530 --> 00:45:04.890
and how many people
have not won so far.

00:45:04.890 --> 00:45:09.610
And what-- And those people who
have won, you know what they won

00:45:09.610 --> 00:45:13.140
because there is-- there are
gradations in the winnings.

00:45:13.140 --> 00:45:16.080
So there's-- there are
techniques and algorithms,

00:45:16.080 --> 00:45:19.890 position:56%
they're not really algorithms,
they're just sort of rational smarts

00:45:19.890 --> 00:45:25.800
that you have to figure out when
to buy the ticket, for scratch-off

00:45:25.800 --> 00:45:29.180
that is, and where
to buy the ticket.

00:45:29.180 --> 00:45:32.960
But that's a lot of work to be
done because you have to do a lot

00:45:32.960 --> 00:45:37.670
of analysis of where
all those, you know,

00:45:37.670 --> 00:45:40.890
7-11s are that you can
buy those tickets from.

00:45:40.890 --> 00:45:46.480
And this doesn't only go
from one little locale.

00:45:46.480 --> 00:45:50.650
It has to be in different places
in a state and different states.

00:45:50.650 --> 00:45:53.400
So, it's a very broad thing
to do but it's a lot of work.

00:45:53.400 --> 00:45:54.700
&gt;&gt; Joel Achenbach: Do
